<h1>Debian/PowerPC</h1>
<p>
 The PowerPC is a RISC (Reduced Instruction-Set Computing) microprocessor
 developed by <a href="http://www.chips.ibm.com/products/powerpc/">IBM</a>
 and <a href="http://mot-sps.com/products/microprocessors/index.html">Motorola</a>.
 The first such chip was the 601, released in 1992. After that, the 603 and
 604 series were developed. The most recent version of the PowerPC
 processor is the 750, also known as the G3.
</p>

<p>
 <center><img src="pics/ppc750.jpg" alt="PPC-750 Bild"></center>
</p>

